.TH "_set_module_autoidle" 9 "_set_module_autoidle" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_set_module_autoidle \- set the OCP_SYSCONFIG AUTOIDLE field in @v
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" _set_module_autoidle
.BI "(struct omap_hwmod *oh "  ","
.BI "u8 autoidle "  ","
.BI "u32 *v "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "oh" 12
struct omap_hwmod *
.IP "autoidle" 12
desired AUTOIDLE bitfield value (0 or 1)
.IP "v" 12
pointer to register contents to modify
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Update the module autoidle bit in \fIv\fP to be \fIautoidle\fP for the \fIoh\fP
hwmod.  The autoidle bit controls whether the module can gate
internal clocks automatically when it isn't doing anything; the
exact function of this bit varies on a per-module basis.  This
function does not write to the hardware.  Returns -EINVAL upon
error or 0 upon success.
